cs.CV, cs.RO, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.IR 

The paper focuses on the development of an autonomous UAV with onboard deep learning inference for animal biometrics and identification. This involves computer vision and navigation, which are key areas of research in computer science. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper also involves robotics (cs.RO) as it deals with the development of an autonomous UAV. The use of deep learning models for animal identification falls under machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). Finally, the paper involves information retrieval (cs.IR) as it deals with the retrieval of information about individual animals from a large dataset.
